The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and databases, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category since it deals with NLP and its applications. cs.DB (Databases) is also a likely category since the paper deals with a natural language interface for databases. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category since the paper uses deep models for query understanding. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category since the paper deals with information extraction from databases. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category since the paper uses machine learning techniques for query understanding.
